From the present analysis we can conclude that GB work function variations decrease upon NH4OH etching and that the surface is cleaned, which results in a higher average work function. At this point we already see that different cleaning/measurement protocols can strongly influence the KPFM results. We do see a substantial change of the GB work functions ΔΘ~GB\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
